<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12695] Truncate ALWAYS not applied</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12695</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If truncate is set to ALWAYS and rate sets a specific thread count, the stress table is not actually truncated. E.g.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;truncate=always -rate threads=4
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can cause an unexpected number of rows to be left in the table.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13007053">CASSANDRA-12695</key>
